This archive is the fixture crate the rust-analyzer integration test
materializes to disk. clean.rs compiles; broken.rs references an undefined
value so rust-analyzer reports one error-severity diagnostic at line 2,
column 13. Both source files are wired as binaries in Cargo.toml so the crate
builds, which rust-analyzer requires before it analyzes them.

-- Cargo.toml --
[package]
name = "fixture"
version = "0.0.0"
edition = "2021"

[[bin]]
name = "clean"
path = "clean.rs"

[[bin]]
name = "broken"
path = "broken.rs"
-- clean.rs --
fn add(a: i32, b: i32) -> i32 {
    a + b
}

fn main() {
    let _ = add(1, 2);
}
-- broken.rs --
fn main() {
    let _ = undefined_symbol + 1;
}
